      <p>What a good trick, Molly!  Now we can all return to this page on those days &#038; scan the comments for an idea.  I did the braised greens-chickpeas last week &#8211; I always end up w/a bunch of greens from the farmer&#39;s market.</p>
<p>Here&#39;s a sample of my list:<br />1. Veggie southern comfort plate: *braised greens, *BBQ-sauce baked tofu, &#038; *doctored-can-of-black-eyed-peas (involves peanut butter, ketchup, mustard &#038; hot sauce!)<br />2.  Spicy red beans &#038; coconut rice, topped w/sour cream &#038; cilantro<br />3.  Black beans on top of either a quesadilla or frozen tamales (Trader Joe&#39;s aren&#39;t bad!) <br />4.  Avocado on toast, w/salt<br />5.  Crackers, cheese, &#038; pear slices<br />6.  Your warm chickpea salad w/carrots<br />7.  Salmon-potato chowder<br />8.  Sweet potato fries (oven-baked) with a veggie or salmon burger<br />9.  Bay shrimp on salad &#8211; avocado &#038; tomato a plus!<br />10. Big pan of enchiladas &#8211; fave filling is: roasted sweet potatoes &#038; red peppers w/cocoa-spiced black beans. <br />11. Easy fish: 2Tbsp lemon juice/2Tbsp honey/2Tbsp dijon mustard: mix in 1 bowl.  2nd bowl: mix panko crumbs &#038; thyme &#038; s/p.  Dip fish in sauce then crumbs, bake ~20 min in 350-75 oven.<br />12.  Baked potato w/broccoli &#038; cheese or baked sweet potato w/sour cream or yogurt.<br />13. &#8220;wacky&#8221; cake &#8211; ie. vegan chocolate cake/depression cake.<br />14. minestrone soup<br />15. &#8220;dream gravy&#8221;- a name a friend coined for a peanut butter-chocolate ice cream sauce</p>
    </div>

